%3EFormer%20Intel%20CEO%20Pat%20Gelsinger%20holding%20up%20a%20chip%20at%20a%20US%20Senate%20hearing.%3Cp%3EGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIntel's%20CEO%20departure%20reignited%20debate%20on%20splitting%20its%20factories%20from%20the%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIntel's%20fabs%20are%20costly%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20considered%20vital%20for%20US%20national%20security.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECHIPS%20Act%20funding%20requires%20Intel%20to%20maintain%20majority%20control%20of%20its%20foundry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20central%20question%20has%20been%20hanging%20over%20Intel%20for%20months%3A%20Should%20the%2056-year-old%20Silicon%20Valley%20legend%20separate%20its%20chip%20factories%2C%20or%20fabs%2C%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20company%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel's%20departing%20CEO%2C%20Pat%20Gelsinger%2C%20has%20opposed%20that%20strategy.%20As%20a%20longtime%20champion%20of%20the%20company's%20chip%20manufacturing%20efforts%2C%20he%20was%20reluctant%20to%20split%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20taken%20some%20steps%20to%20look%20into%20this%20strategy.%20Bloomberg%20reported%20in%20August%20that%20Intel%20had%20hired%20bankers%20to%20help%20consider%20several%20options%2C%20including%20splitting%20off%20the%20fabs%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20Intel.%20The%20company%20also%20announced%20in%20September%20that%20it%20would%20establish%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-pat-gelsinger-turnaround-plan-aws-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFoundry%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20separate%20subsidiary%20within%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGelsinger's%20departure%20from%20the%20company%2C%20announced%20Monday%2C%20has%20reopened%20the%20question%2C%20although%20the%20calculus%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20simple%20dollars%20and%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESplitting%20the%20fabs%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20its%20business%20could%20help%20Intel%20improve%20its%20balance%20sheet.%20It%20likely%20won't%20be%20easy%20since%20Intel%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-chips-act-award-grant-biden-administration-semiconductor-trump-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eawarded%20%247.9%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchips-act-top-lobbyists-chip-companies-nvidia-tsmc-intel-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20funding%2C%20and%20it's%20required%20to%20maintain%20majority%20control%20of%20its%20foundries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e7ca66f-e6a6-49f5-8bce-d00a6ae7e9d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20breakup%20could%20make%20Intel%20more%20competitive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-qualcomm-odd-couple-wont-solve-us-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPolitically%2C%20fabs%20are%20important%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20Intel's%20place%20in%20the%20American%20economy%20and%20allow%20the%20US%20to%20reduce%20dependence%20on%20foreign%20manufacturers.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20they%20drag%20down%20the%20company's%20balance%20sheet.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-dow-jones-ai-chip-lag-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIntel's%20foundry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20line%20of%20business%20that%20manufactures%20chips%2C%20has%20posted%20losses%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFabs%20are%20immensely%20hard%20work.%20They're%20expensive%20to%20build%20and%20operate%2C%20and%20they%20require%20a%20level%20of%20precision%20beyond%20most%20other%20types%20of%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20could%20benefit%20from%20a%20split%2C%20and%20the%20company%20maintains%20meaningful%20market%20share%20in%20its%20computing%20and%20traditional%20(not%20AI)%20data%20center%20businesses.%20Amid%20the%20broader%20CEO%20search%2C%20Intel%20also%20elevated%20executive%20Michelle%20Johnston%20Holthaus%20to%20CEO%20of%20Intel%20Products%20and%20the%20company's%20co-CEO.%20Analysts%20said%20this%20could%20better%20set%20up%20a%20split.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20analysts%20said%20finding%20new%20leadership%20for%20the%20fabs%20will%20be%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20choice%20for%20any%20new%20CEO%20would%20seem%20to%20center%20on%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20fabs%2C%26quot%3B%20Bernstein%20analysts%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20to%20investors%20after%20the%20announcement%20of%20Gelsinger's%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20fabs%20are%20%26quot%3Bdeadweight%26quot%3B%20for%20Intel%2C%20the%20Bernstein%20analysts%20wrote.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20%26quot%3Bscrapping%20them%20would%20also%20be%20fraught%20with%20difficulties%20around%20the%20product%20road%20map%2C%20outsourcing%20strategy%2C%20CHIPS%20Act%20and%20political%20navigation%2C%20etc.%20There%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20any%20easy%20answers%20here%2C%20so%20whoever%20winds%20up%20filling%20the%20slot%20looks%20in%20for%20a%20tough%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel's%20competitors%20and%20contemporaries%20are%20avoiding%20the%20hassle%20of%20owning%20and%20operating%20a%20fab.%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20world's%20leading%20chip%20design%20firm%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-taiwan-tsmc-jensen-huang-china-disruption-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENvidia%2C%20outsources%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0all%20its%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Its%20runner-up%2C%20AMD%2C%20experienced%20similar%20woes%20when%20it%20owned%20fabs%2C%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-amd-nvidia-chip-manufacturing-moores-law-fabless-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espinning%20them%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20also%20outsourced%20some%20chip%20manufacturing%20to%20rival%20TSMC%20in%20recent%20years%20%E2%80%94%20which%20sends%20a%20negative%20signal%20to%20the%20market%20about%20its%20own%20fabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ffc1777c-08e0-4604-82ad-9cb83cb5fc05%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntel%20is%20getting%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOwnership%20of%20the%20fabs%20and%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding%20are%20highly%20intertwined.%20Intel%20must%20retain%20majority%20control%20of%20the%20foundry%20to%20continue%20receiving%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding%20and%20benefits%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.intc.com%2Ffilings-reports%2Fall-sec-filings%2Fcontent%2F0000050863-24-000169%2F0000050863-24-000169.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENovember%20regulatory%20filing%20said.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20could%20separate%20its%20foundry%20business%20while%20maintaining%20majority%20control%2C%20said%20Dan%20Newman%2C%20CEO%20of%20The%20Futurum%20Group.%20Still%2C%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%20remains%20key%20to%20Intel's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20add%20it%20all%20up%2C%20it%20equates%20to%20roughly%20%2440%20billion%20in%20loans%2C%20tax%20exemptions%2C%20and%20grants%20%E2%80%94%20so%20quite%20significant%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Logan%20Purk%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20Edward%20Jones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnly%20a%20small%20slice%20of%20the%20commitment%20has%20come%2C%20though%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dbca24d3-22e5-4ccb-9587-a0e1f50ebaa0%5C%22%3EIntel's%20fabs%20need%20more%20customers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20is%20attempting%20to%20move%20beyond%20manufacturing%20its%20own%20chips%20to%20becoming%20a%20contract%20manufacturer.%20Amazon%20has%20already%20signed%20on%20as%20a%20customer.%20Though%20bringing%20in%20more%20manufacturing%20customers%20could%20mean%20more%20revenue%2C%20it%20first%20requires%20more%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20more%20ephemeral%20reason%20Intel%20might%20want%20separation%20between%20its%20Foundry%20and%20its%20chip%20design%20businesses%2C%20too.%20Foundries%20regularly%20deal%20with%20many%20competing%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20big%20concerns%20for%20the%20fabless%20designers%20is%20any%20sort%20of%20information%20leakage%2C%26quot%3B%20Newman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20products%20department%20competes%20with%20many%20potential%20clients%20of%20the%20foundry.%20You%20want%20separation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20once%20rumored%20that%20a%20third%20party%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fqualcomm-considers-intel-buyout-analysts-see-major-hurdles-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy%20Intel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Analysts%20have%20balked%20at%20the%20prospect%20for%20political%20and%20financial%20reasons%2C%20particularly%20since%20running%20the%20fabs%20is%20a%20major%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-exit-reignites-fab-foundry-debacle-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733266443000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674f6c8def9a5d904789c10a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-exit-reignites-fab-foundry-debacle-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Intel's%20CEO%20exit%20reignites%20discussions%20on%20splitting%20off%20factories%2C%20with%20questions%20about%20financial%20recovery%20and%20CHIPS%20Act%20funding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ecosgrove%40businessinsider.com%20(Emma%20Cosgrove)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A40%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-ceo-exit-reignites-fab-foundry-debacle-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20public%20school%20teacher%20with%20a%