artial%20law%20in%20the%20country%2C%20South%20Korean%20President%20Yoon%20Suk%20Yeol%20said%20he%20will%20withdraw%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%204%3A30%20am%20(local%20time)%20special%20address%20to%20the%20nation%2C%20President%20Yoon%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BJust%20a%20moment%20ago%2C%20there%20was%20a%20demand%20from%20the%20National%20Assembly%20to%20lift%20the%20state%20of%20emergency%2C%20and%20we%20have%20withdrawn%20the%20military%20that%20was%20deployed%20for%20martial%20law%20operations.%20We%20will%20accept%20the%20National%20Assembly's%20request%20and%20lift%20the%20martial%20law%20through%20the%20Cabinet%20meeting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korean%20MPs%20had%20voted%20unanimously%20against%20the%20imposition%20of%20martial%20law%20at%20a%20midnight%20session%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20to%20denounce%20the%20President's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20President%20then%20agreed%20to%20honour%20the%20vote%2C%20as%20did%20the%20army%20chief.%20Shortly%20after%20the%20President%20withdrew%20the%20order%20and%20addressed%20the%20nation%2C%20the%20South%20Korean%20cabinet%20convened%20for%20a%205%20am%20(local%20time)%20meeting%20to%20approve%20a%20motion%20to%20officially%20lift%20what%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20shortest-ever%20martial%20laws%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20events%20unfolded%20in%20the%20intervening%20night%20of%20Tuesday%20and%20Wednesday%20in%20Korea%2C%20President%20Yoon's%20decision%20for%20a%20national%20emergency%20and%20martial%20law%20was%20vehemently%20opposed%20by%20parliamentarians%20who%20rejected%20the%20decision%20to%20ban%20political%20activity%20and%20censor%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20his%20move%2C%20President%20Yoon%20had%20said%20that%20the%20decision%20was%20taken%20to%20crush%20%26quot%3Banti-state%20forces%26quot%3B.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%20in%20nearly%20five%20decades%20that%20South%20Korea%20had%20imposed%20a%20martial%20law%20-%20the%20last%20one%20being%20in%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoliticians%20and%20protesters%20had%20assembled%20outside%20the%20National%20Assembly%20(Parliament)%20shouting%20slogans%20in%20defiance%20of%20the%20martial%20law%20that%20was%20in%20place%20at%20the%20time.%20Security%20forces%20had%20to%20fire%20tear%20gas%20shells%20to%20disperse%20the%20crowd.%20The%20country's%20currency%20also%20went%20on%20a%20downward%20spiral.%20However%2C%20the%20situation%20improved%20after%20President%20Yoon%20agreed%20to%20the%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20and%20said%20he%20will%20announce%20the%20withdrawal%20shortly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korea%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20economies%20of%20Asia%20and%20is%20a%20key%20ally%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20It%20has%20also%20been%20a%20democracy%20for%20more%20than%20four%20decades.%20The%20move%20to%20enforce%20a%20martial%20law%20had%20therefore%20caused%20international%20alarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20South%20Korea%20is%20under%20a%20constant%20threat%20from%20its%20northern%20nuclear-armed%20neighbour%20North%20Korea%2C%20President%20Yoon%20did%20not%20suggest%20any%20specific%20threat%20from%20Kim%20Jong-Un%20that%20could%20have%20led%20to%20this%20sudden%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Yoon%20has%20been%20under%20pressure%20in%20domestic%20politics%20after%20his%20party%20-%20People%20Power%20Party%20-%20suffered%20a%20massive%20defeat%20in%20the%20general%20election%20held%20in%20April%20this%20year.%20The%20result%20left%20the%20opposition%20with%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20Parlaiment.%20President%20Yoon%20has%20also%20been%20rather%20unpopular%20in%20recent%20times%2C%20with%20his%20national%20rating%20falling%20to%20just%20around%2020%20per%20cent.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733261160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fjn2mdvo8_south-korea-president-yoon-suk-yeol-reuters_625x300_04_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%